The prompt section (around lines 135-254) shows definePrompt with a manual arguments array. Add a new subsection after the existing prompt examples showing the typed variant:

### Typed Prompts with Zod Schema

Instead of manually defining the `arguments` array, you can pass a Zod `args` schema. The MCP metadata (argument names, descriptions, required flags) is auto-generated from the schema at build time, and `render()` receives typed arguments:

```typescript
import { definePrompt } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';
import { z } from 'zod';

const statusReport = definePrompt({
  name: 'status_report',
  description: 'Generate a project status report',
  args: z.object({
    project: z.string().describe('Project name'),
    format: z.enum(['brief', 'detailed']).describe('Report format'),
  }),
  async render(args) {
    // args is typed as { project: string; format: 'brief' | 'detailed' }
    return [{ role: 'user', content: { type: 'text', text: `Status for ${args.project} (${args.format})` } }];
  },
});
```

