### Typed Resources with Schema

Resources can include an optional Zod `schema` for type-safe content. The schema provides a type-level contract — the runtime dispatch path does not validate against it:

```typescript
import { defineResource } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';
import { z } from 'zod';

const channelList = defineResource({
  uri: 'myapp://channels',
  name: 'Channel List',
  description: 'All active channels',
  mimeType: 'application/json',
  schema: z.object({
    channels: z.array(z.object({ id: z.string(), name: z.string() })),
  }),
  async read() {
    const data = await fetchJSON('/api/channels');
    return { uri: 'myapp://channels', text: JSON.stringify(data) };
  },
});
```

